wing command   at a DB2 Command Line Processor prompt:   <strong class="userinput"><span>db2 &#039;? <code class="parameter">sqlstate-value</span>&#039;</code></strong>. You   can also call <span class="function">{@link db2_conn_errormsg()}</span> to retrieve an   explicit error message and the associated SQLCODE value.  </p> </div> <br></br><div style="BORDER-TOP: gray 1px dashed; OVERFLOW: hidden; HEIGHT: 1px"></div><div class="refsect1 parameters" id="refsect1-function.db2-conn-error-parameters">  <h3 class="title">参数</h3>  <span>   <dl>         <dt><span class="parameter" style="color:#3A95FF">connection</span></dt>     <dd>      <p class="para">       A connection resource associated with a connection that initially       succeeded, but which over time became invalid.      </p>     </dd>       </dl>  </span> </div> <br></br><div style="BORDER-TOP: gray 1px dashed; OVERFLOW: hidden; HEIGHT: 1px"></div><div class="refsect1 returnvalues" id="refsect1-function.db2-conn-error-returnvalues">  <h3 class="title">返回值</h3>  <p class="para">   Returns the SQLSTATE value resulting from a failed connection attempt.   Returns an empty string if there is no error associated with the last   connection attempt.  </p> </div> <br></br><div style="BORDER-TOP: gray 1px dashed; OVERFLOW: hidden; HEIGHT: 1px"></div><div class="refsect1 examples" id="refsect1-function.db2-conn-error-examples">  <h3 class="title">示例</h3>  <span>   <div class="example" id="example-3752">    <p><strong>示例 #1 Retrieving an SQLSTATE value for a failed connection attempt</strong></p>    <div class="example-contents"><p>     The following example demonstrates how to return an SQLSTATE value      after deliberately passing invalid parameters to     <span class="function">{@link db2_connect()}</span>.    </p></div>    <div class="example-contents"><div class="phpcode" style="border-color:gray;background:#232525"><span><span style="color: #000000"><span style="color: #9876AA">&lt;?php<br />$conn </span><span style="color: #007700">= </span><span style="color: #9876AA">db2_connect</span><span style="color: #007700">(</span><span style="color: #DD0000">'badname'</span><span style="color: #007700">, </span><span style="color: #DD0000">'baduser'</span><span style="color: #007700">, </span><span style="color: #DD0000">'badpassword'</span><span style="color: #007700">);<br />if (!</span><span style="color: #9876AA">$conn</span><span style="color: #007700">) {<br />    print </span><span style="color: #DD0000">"SQLSTATE value: " </span><span style="color: #007700">. </span><span style="color: #9876AA">db2_conn_error</span><span style="color: #007700">();<br />}<br /></span><span style="color: #9876AA">?&gt;</span></span></span></div>    </div>    <div class="example-contents"><p>以上示例会输出：</p></div>    <div class="example-contents screen" style="color:AFB1B3;background:black;padding-left:5px;"><div class="cdata"><span>SQLSTATE value: 08001<br></span></div>    </div>   </div>  </span> </div> <br></br><div style="BORDER-TOP: gray 1px dashed; OVERFLOW: hidden; HEIGHT: 1px"></div><div class="refsect1 seealso" id="refsect1-function.db2-conn-error-seealso">  <h3 class="title">参见</h3>  <span>   <ul class="simplelist">    <li class="member"><span class="function">{@link db2_conn_errormsg()} - Returns the last connection error message and SQLCODE value</span></li>    <li class="member"><span class="function">{@link db2_connect()} - Returns a connection to a database</span></li>    <li class="member"><span class="function">{@link db2_stmt_error()} - Returns a string containing the SQLSTATE returned by an SQL statement</span></li>    <li class="member"><span class="function">{@link db2_stmt_errormsg()} - Returns a string containing the last SQL statement error message</span></li>   </ul>  </span> </div></div>
 * @return string the SQLSTATE value resulting from a failed connection attempt.*/
